  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped carrots and celery and cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the brown lentils, diced tomatoes, vegetable broth, mild curry powder, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.",
    "Use an immersion blender to puree the stew to your desired consistency.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Refrigerate or freeze any leftovers for later use."
